card.desc:
Beachbum Berry’s Mai Tai
------------------------

1 rum, dark (Appleton Estate Extra Dark Jamaican or Banks 5 Island)
1 rhum agricole (Rhum Clément VSOP)
1 lime juice
1/2 curaçao, orange (Marie Brizard)
1/2 orgeat (Latitude 29 Formula Orgeat or Kassatly Chtaura)
1/4 simple syrup
Rocks glass w/ pebble ice
Mint sprig

—Bergeron, Jules. (1947). *Trader Vic's Bartender's Guide.*

Smuggler’s Cove Mai Tai
-----------------------

2 rum, aged (Denizen Marchant’s Reserve 8, Appleton Estate 12yr or El Dorado 12yr)
3/4 lime juice
1/2 orange curaçao or orange liqueur (Cointreau)
1/4 rock candy syrup (2 parts rock candy, 1 part water) or demerara syrup
1/4 orgeat almond syrup
Shake w/ crushed ice, pour unstrained into rocks glass
Lime juice & mint sprig

—Cate, Martin. (2000s). Smuggier's Cove, San Francisco.

Lost Lake’s Mai Tai
-------------------

1/2 rum, dark, Jamaican (Plantation Xamayca)
1/2 rum, dark, overproof (Smith & Cross)
1 rhum agricole (Neisson Eleve Sous Bois Rhum Agricole)
1 lime juice
1/2 curaçao, orange (Pierre Ferrand)
3/4 orgeat (Small Hand Foods)
1/4 syrup, demerara, 2:1
Shake w/ lime hull
Rocks glass w/ pebble ice
Mint sprig

—Suderman, Peter. (2022). *Cocktails With Suderman.*

old.desc:
[1]

Note:

  - Simple: spirit, ice, lengthener
  - Complex: add juice/liqeur
  - Collins: add lemon juice and sugar
  - Fizzes: shaken, served no ice

Gin & Tonic
-----------

Gin
Top w/ tonic water
Lime
Bitters

Dark & Stormy
-------------

2 rum, dark
4 ginger beer (topped)
3/4 lime juice

Monkey Gland
------------

2 gin (Beefeater)
1 orange juice
1 barspoon grenadine
Absinthe rinse

—McElhone, Harry. (1922). *ABC of Mixing Cocktails.* Ciro's Club, London.

### Swollen Gland

Sub yellow chartreuse & bitters, Peychaud's for grenadine
Cucumber ribbon on pick

—Meehan, Jim, & Reissmueller, Lydia. (2009, Fall). PDT, New York.

Moscow Mule
-----------

1 1/2 vodka (Smirnoff Black)
2 ginger beer
3/4 lime juice
Shake, strain into mule cup w/ ice
Lime wheel

—Beebe, Lucius. (1946). *Stork Club Bar Book, The.* Morgan, Jack (bartender) Cock 'n' Bull, Los Angeles.

Cuba Libre
----------

Rum
Top w/ Cola
Lime

Harvey Wallbanger
-----------------

4 Vodka
1 Galliano
Top w/ Orange juice

Paloma
------

2 tequila
1/2 lime juice
Build in salt-rimmed Collins glass w/ ice
Top w/ 2 oz Mexican Squirt or Tin Grapefruit Soda
Grapefruit wheel

—Wondrich, David. (2005). *Killer Cocktails.*

This exotic sipper from Imbibe's 2013 Cocktail Bar of the Year, Pouring Ribbons, (see the "Imbibe 75" feature in our January/February issue) is a little smoky, a little nutty and perfectly bright.

1 1/2 oz. mezcal
3/4 oz. Palo Cortado sherry
3/4 oz. orgeat
1/2 oz. fresh lemon juice
1/2 oz. pineapple juice
Tools: shaker, strainer
Glass: rocks
Garnish: cocoa powder

In a shaker, combine ingredients and shake with ice cubes until chilled. Strain into a rocks glass over fresh ice cubes (or one large cube). Dust with cocoa powder.

1 sweet vermouth (Martini)
Coupe or rocks glass w/ ice

2 gin

1 bitter wine aperitif (e.g. Lillet, Cocchi Americano, Kina)

Kingston Negroni
----------------

Sub gin w/ rum, amber (Smith & Cross)

—Simo, Joaquin. (2009). Death & Company, New York.

Lucky
-----

1 ½ gin (St. George Terroir)
1 bitter apertivo (Salers)
½ chartreuse, green
2 dash bitters, celery
Lemon peel

1 gin
1 rye
1 amaro, grassy/herbal (e.g. Cynar, Bonal)
1 amaro, floral (e.g. Gran Classico, Meletti)
2 bitters, tiki (allspice/cinnamon)

1 Warwick, 1 Templeton, 1/2 Cynar, 1/2 Gran Classico, 1/4 Dolin Rouge, 2 dash Bitter Truth Aromatic

### Attempt 2

3/4 Warwick, 3/4 Templeton, 1/2 Cynar, 1/2 Gran Classico, 1/2 Dolin Rouge, 1 dash Bitter Truth Aromatic, 1 dash Allspice Bitters

Float w/ green chartreuse

------

2 gin (Plymouth)
3/4 lemon juice
3/4 simple syrup

Fitzgerald
----------

Add bitters

Southside
---------

Muddle 4 mint leaves w/ syrup

Gimlet
------

2 gin (Plymouth)
3/4 lime juice

Lime wheel

24 simple syrup
Zest of 12 limes
Infuse for 10m
Strain, bottle, & refrigerate

Lemon twist

1 750 ml gin (Tanqueray)
4 tbsp Earl Grey tea, loose
Shake, sit, room temp., 2 hr
Strain

—Saunders, Audrey. (2004). "State of the Cocktail, The." *New York Magazine.*
